The paper proposes a new technique to analyze timed systems using finite tree automata, which suggests that it could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of MSO-definable properties, which further supports this categorization. Additionally, the paper deals with pushdown systems, which could place it in the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The use of tree-width and graph theory suggests that it could also belong to the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of boundedness restrictions, which could place it in the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with timed systems, which could place it in the Logic and Verification (cs.LT) sub-category.
